\begin_layout Subsection*
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This policy establishes the governance structure,
 methodology,
 and responsibilities for managing information technology risk within Elko County.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This policy applies to all information systems,
 infrastructure,
 data,
 personnel,
 and third-party vendors managed by or on behalf of the Elko County Information Operations Department (ECIO).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
IT Director:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Shall serve as the designated 
\series bold
Authorizing Official (AO)
\series default
 for Elko County,
 with authority to issue risk-based authorization decisions for all County information systems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall serve as the 
\series bold
Chief Information Security Officer (CISO)
\series default
 for the County.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall define the County's risk tolerance by reviewing and approving the 
\series bold
Risk Management Strategy
\series default
 at least annually.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall approve all 
\series bold
Risk Acceptance Memos
\series default
 in accordance with the governance requirements defined in Section 6.8.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall review and formally approve System Security Categorizations.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Assistant IT Director:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Shall serve as the 
\series bold
Risk Program Owner
\series default
 and coordinate Risk Management Framework (RMF) evidence across systems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall ensure the accuracy and currency of the centralized 
\series bold
Risk Register
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall develop and maintain a documented Risk Management Strategy that defines risk appetite and tolerance,
 prioritization criteria,
 management decision rules for selecting risk responses,
 scoring methodology,
 reporting thresholds,
 and review cadence (NIST SP 800-53 Rev.
 5:
 PM-9 (Risk Management Strategy)).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall oversee the execution of risk assessments and vulnerability scans.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall validate that risk mitigation strategies and 
\series bold
Corrective Action Plans
\series default
 tracked under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Compliance Monitoring and Corrective Action) are effective and updated.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Systems Administrators and Network Administrators:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Shall conduct technical risk assessments and vulnerability scans within their operational domain.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall implement required risk mitigation controls and remediate vulnerabilities within mandated timelines.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall populate and update technical risk entries in the Risk Register — including Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVE) data,
