 vulnerability status,
 and treatment progress — for controls within their operational domain.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall report changes in system architecture that may alter the risk profile to the Assistant IT Director within one (1) business day.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
All Information Operations Personnel:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Shall submit identified vulnerabilities,
 control gaps,
 or potential threats to the Assistant IT Director for inclusion in the Risk Register.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall report active threats,
 anomalous system behavior,
 or suspected breaches immediately via the channels defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Identification and Reporting Procedures).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall adhere to risk mitigation procedures and security controls defined in this manual.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Department Heads and Elected Officials:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Shall support the categorization of information systems within their purview and participate in risk assessments when requested by the IT Director or Assistant IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shall concur with Risk Acceptance Memos for systems within their purview,
