\begin_layout Subsubsection*
6.5 Risk Response Strategies
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Upon identification of a risk,
 the Assistant IT Director shall select one of the following response strategies (NIST SP 800-53 Rev.
 5:
 RA-7 (Risk Response)):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Mitigate
\series default
:
 The responsible Administrator shall apply controls (patches,
 configuration changes,
 and physical barriers) to reduce risk to an acceptable level.
 When the mitigation response requires tracked remediation with milestones,
 the Assistant IT Director shall route it to 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 for Corrective Action Plan development.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Accept
\series default
:
 Formally acknowledge the risk in accordance with the Risk Acceptance Governance requirements defined in Section 6.8.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Transfer
\series default
:
 Shift liability to a third party (e.g.,
 cyber insurance,
 managed service contracts).
 The Assistant IT Director shall manage vendor risk transfer in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Avoid
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall authorize discontinuation of the activity,
 system,
 or vendor relationship causing the risk.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
6.6 Criticality Analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Assistant IT Director shall identify critical system components and functions by performing a criticality analysis at the planning,
 design,
 and implementation stages (NIST SP 800-53 Rev.
 5:
 RA-9 (Criticality Analysis)).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
High Value Assets (HVAs)
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall designate systems as Critical or High Value in the Disaster Recovery Plan or System Security Plan (SSP).
 The Assistant IT Director shall prioritize designated systems for advanced protection measures and continuity planning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
6.7 Risk Register and Reporting
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Assistant IT Director shall maintain a centralized Risk Register tracking all identified risks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
System of Record
\series default
:
 The Risk Register shall be maintained in the Department's designated 
\series bold
System of Engagement
\series default
 with strict role-based access controls.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Sensitive Security Information
\series default
:
 The Risk Register and supporting evidence shall be treated as sensitive security documentation.
 The Assistant IT Director shall restrict access to authorized personnel on a need-to-know basis and shall manage disclosures in accordance with County policy and CJIS requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Minimum Data Fields
\series default
:
 The Risk Register shall contain,
 at a minimum:
 Risk ID,
 Date Identified,
 System/Asset,
 System Owner,
 CJI Indicator (Y/N),
 Risk Category,
 CVE/CVSS (if applicable),
 Inherent/Residual Score,
 Control Mapping,
 Treatment Strategy,
 CAP Linkage (when applicable),
 Status,
 Due Date,
 and Acceptance Authority.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
CAP Updates
\series default
:
 Corrective Action Plans for unremediated risks shall follow the tracking and update cadence defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The Assistant IT Director shall update the corresponding Risk Register entry when a CAP achieves closure or when a CAP milestone changes the residual risk posture.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Reporting
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall report a summary of the County's risk posture — including all accepted High and Critical risks — to the County Manager annually.
 Risk posture data shall also be provided as an input to the annual policy review and maturity scoring process under 
\series bold
Policy 
