\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
6.8 Risk Acceptance Governance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Risk acceptance is a formal risk response strategy that requires documented justification,
 dual concurrence,
 and IT Director approval.
 This section defines the governance framework for risk acceptance decisions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Risk Acceptance Memo
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall document each risk acceptance in a Risk Acceptance Memo.
 Each memo shall include,
 at a minimum:
 scope of the accepted risk,
 business justification,
 compensating controls,
 expiration or review date,
 residual risk statement,
 and the concurrence of the Department Head or Elected Official responsible for the affected system.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Decision Rights
\series default
:
 Department Head or Elected Official concurrence constitutes acknowledgment of operational and business impact and acceptance of residual operational risk.
 IT Director (AO) approval constitutes the authorization decision and acceptance of residual security risk on behalf of the County.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Approval Authority
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall approve all Risk Acceptance Memos.
 Risk acceptance is non-delegable.
 No other role may approve risk acceptance on the IT Director's behalf,
 consistent with the non-delegable functions defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Automatic Expiration
\series default
:
 All risk acceptances shall automatically expire on the stated expiration date.
 The Assistant IT Director shall treat expired acceptances as unauthorized deviations until renewed in writing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Ongoing Monitoring
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall monitor accepted risks for changes in likelihood,
 impact,
 or exposure until the risk is closed or the acceptance expires.
 Accepted risks shall remain documented in the Risk Register.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Prohibition
\series default
:
 Risk acceptance shall not authorize non-compliance with CJIS Security Policy requirements,
 statutory requirements,
 or other mandatory security controls.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Authorization Package
\series default
:
 Risk Acceptance Memos shall become part of the system's authorization package alongside the System Security Plan,
 Security Assessment Report,
 and any open Corrective Action Plans.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Record Retention
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall retain Risk Acceptance Memos,
 risk assessment reports,
 and supporting evidence in accordance with NRS 239.125 and the applicable Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedule under NAC 239.155,
 including records classified under the IT Security Evaluations,
 IT Security Plans,
 and IT Security Reviews,
 Reports and Logs series.
\end_layout

